{
  "texts": [
    "We call this problem conditional task generation.",
    "Our key idea is to make a new largescale dataset called Conditional Task Generation with Attributes (CTGA), to train Bonito, by reorganizing existing instruction tuning datasets (see Figure 2).",
    "Instruction tuning datasets like P3 (Bach et al., 2022) exist as templates that convert semistructured examples of natural language tasks into a fully prompted format, in which both the input and the desired response are text strings.",
    "We focus on a subset of the templates in P3 that require a context or a passage to complete the task.",
    "For example, a context could be a paragraph that contains a fact or that contains the answer to a question."
  ]
}